#, no-wrap
msgid "\\(bu"
msgstr "\\(bu"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:27
msgid ""
"Source files are preserved by default. It\\'s possible to remove them "
"automatically by using the B<--rm> command."
msgstr "默认情况下会保留源文件。可以使用 B<--rm> 命令自动删除它们。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:30
msgid ""
"When compressing a single file, B<zstd> displays progress notifications and "
"result summary by default. Use B<-q> to turn them off."
msgstr ""
"在压缩单个文件时，B<zstd> 默认会显示进度通知和结果摘要。使用 B<-q> 可将其关"
"闭。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:33
msgid ""
"B<zstd> displays a short help page when command line is an error. Use B<-q> "
"to turn it off."
msgstr ""
"当命令行有误时，B<zstd> 会显示一个简短的帮助页面。使用 B<-q> 可将其关闭。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:36
msgid ""
"B<zstd> does not accept input from console, though it does accept B<stdin> "
"when it\\'s not the console."
msgstr ""
"B<zstd> 不接受来自控制台的输入，但当 B<stdin> 不是控制台时，它会接受来自 "
"B<stdin> 的输入。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:39
msgid ""
"B<zstd> does not store the input\\'s filename or attributes, only its "
"contents."
msgstr "B<zstd> 不会保存输入的文件名或属性，只保存其内容。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:44
msgid ""
"B<zstd> processes each I<file> according to the selected operation mode. If "
"no I<files> are given or I<file> is B<->, B<zstd> reads from standard input "
"and writes the processed data to standard output. B<zstd> will refuse to "
"write compressed data to standard output if it is a terminal: it will "
"display an error message and skip the file. Similarly, B<zstd> will refuse "
"to read compressed data from standard input if it is a terminal."
msgstr ""
"B<zstd> 会根据所选的操作模式处理每个 I<file>。如果没有给出 I<files>，或者 "
"I<file> 为 B<->，则 B<zstd> 从标准输入读取，并将处理后的数据写入标准输出。如"
"果标准输出是终端，B<zstd> 将拒绝向其写入压缩数据：它会显示一条错误消息并跳过"
"该文件。类似地，如果标准输入是终端，B<zstd> 也将拒绝从中读取压缩数据。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:47
msgid ""
"Unless B<--stdout> or B<-o> is specified, I<files> are written to a new file "
"whose name is derived from the source I<file> name:"
msgstr ""
"除非指定了 B<--stdout> 或 B<-o>，否则 I<files> 会被写入一个新文件，其名称由"
"源 I<file> 名称派生而来："

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:50
msgid ""
"When compressing, the suffix B<.zst> is appended to the source filename to "
"get the target filename."
msgstr "压缩时，会在源文件名后附加 B<.zst> 后缀以得到目标文件名。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:53
msgid ""
"When decompressing, the B<.zst> suffix is removed from the source filename "
"to get the target filename"
msgstr "解压缩时，会从源文件名中移除 B<.zst> 后缀以得到目标文件名"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Concatenation with .zst Files"
msgstr "拼接 .zst 文件"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:58
msgid ""
"It is possible to concatenate multiple B<.zst> files. B<zstd> will "
"decompress such agglomerated file as if it was a single B<.zst> file."
msgstr ""
"可以将多个 B<.zst> 文件拼接在一起。B<zstd> 会将这样拼接而成的文件当作单个 "
"B<.zst> 文件进行解压缩。"

#. type: SH
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "OPTIONS"
msgstr "选项"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Integer Suffixes and Special Values"
msgstr "整数后缀与特殊值"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:63
msgid ""
"In most places where an integer argument is expected, an optional suffix is "
"supported to easily indicate large integers. There must be no space between "
"the integer and the suffix."
msgstr ""
"在大多数需要整数参数的地方，都支持使用可选的后缀来方便地表示较大的整数。整数"
"与后缀之间不能有空格。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<KiB>"
msgstr "B<KiB>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:67
msgid ""
"Multiply the integer by 1,024 (2^10). B<Ki>, B<K>, and B<KB> are accepted as "
"synonyms for B<KiB>."
msgstr ""
"将整数乘以 1,024（2^10）。B<Ki>、B<K> 和 B<KB> 都可作为 B<KiB> 的同义词。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<MiB>"
msgstr "B<MiB>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:71
msgid ""
"Multiply the integer by 1,048,576 (2^20). B<Mi>, B<M>, and B<MB> are "
"accepted as synonyms for B<MiB>."
msgstr ""
"将整数乘以 1,048,576（2^20）。B<Mi>、B<M> 和 B<MB> 都可作为 B<MiB> 的同义词。"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "Operation Mode"
msgstr "操作模式"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:74
msgid ""
"If multiple operation mode options are given, the last one takes effect."
msgstr "如果给出了多个操作模式选项，则以最后一个为准。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-z>, B<--compress>"
msgstr "B<-z>, B<--compress>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:78
msgid ""
"Compress. This is the default operation mode when no operation mode option "
"is specified and no other operation mode is implied from the command name "
"(for example, B<unzstd> implies B<--decompress>)."
msgstr ""
"压缩。当未指定操作模式选项，且命令名称也未隐含其他操作模式时（例如 B<unzstd> "
"隐含 B<--decompress>），这是默认的操作模式。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-d>, B<--decompress>, B<--uncompress>"
msgstr "B<-d>, B<--decompress>, B<--uncompress>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:82
msgid "Decompress."
msgstr "解压缩。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-t>, B<--test>"
msgstr "B<-t>, B<--test>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:86
msgid ""
"Test the integrity of compressed I<files>. This option is equivalent to B<--"
"decompress --stdout E<gt> /dev/null>, decompressed data is discarded and "
"checksummed for errors. No files are created or removed."
msgstr ""
"测试压缩 I<files> 的完整性。此选项等效于 B<--decompress --stdout E<gt> /dev/"
"null>，解压缩后的数据会被丢弃，并进行校验和计算以检查错误。不会创建或删除任何"
"文件。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-b#>"
msgstr "B<-b#>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:90
msgid ""
"Benchmark file(s) using compression level I<#>. See I<BENCHMARK> below for a "
"description of this operation."
msgstr ""
"使用压缩级别 I<#> 对文件进行基准测试。有关此操作的说明，请参见下方的 "
"I<BENCHMARK>（基准测试）一节。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<--train FILES>"
msgstr "B<--train FILES>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:94
msgid ""
"Use I<FILES> as a training set to create a dictionary. The training set "
"should contain a lot of small files (E<gt> 100). See I<DICTIONARY BUILDER> "
"below for a description of this operation."
msgstr ""
"使用 I<FILES> 作为训练集来创建字典。训练集应包含大量小文件（E<gt> 100 个）。"
"有关此操作的说明，请参见下方的 I<DICTIONARY BUILDER>（字典构建器）一节。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:95
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-l>, B<--list>"
msgstr "B<-l>, B<--list>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:98
msgid ""
"Display information related to a zstd compressed file, such as size, ratio, "
"and checksum. Some of these fields may not be available. This command\\'s "
"output can be augmented with the B<-v> modifier."
msgstr ""
"显示与 zstd 压缩文件相关的信息，例如大小、压缩率和校验和。其中某些字段可能不"
"可用。此命令的输出可以通过 B<-v> 修饰符加以扩充。"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "Operation Modifiers"
msgstr "操作修饰符"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:103
msgid ""
"B<-#>: selects B<#> compression level [1-19] (default: 3). Higher "
"compression levels I<generally> produce higher compression ratio at the "
"expense of speed and memory. A rough rule of thumb is that compression speed "
"is expected to be divided by 2 every 2 levels. Technically, each level is "
"mapped to a set of advanced parameters (that can also be modified "
"individually, see below). Because the compressor\\'s behavior highly depends "
"on the content to compress, there\\'s no guarantee of a smooth progression "
"from one level to another."
msgstr ""
"B<-#>：选择 B<#> 压缩级别 [1-19]（默认值：3）。更高的压缩级别 I<通常> 会以速"
"度和内存为代价换取更高的压缩率。一条粗略的经验法则是，压缩级别每提高 2 级，压"
"缩速度预计会减半。从技术上讲，每个级别都会映射到一组高级参数（这些参数也可以"
"单独修改，参见下文）。由于压缩器的行为在很大程度上取决于要压缩的内容，因此无"
"法保证从一个级别到另一个级别是平滑过渡的。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:106
msgid ""
"B<--ultra>: unlocks high compression levels 20+ (maximum 22), using a lot "
"more memory. Note that decompression will also require more memory when "
"using these levels."
msgstr ""
"B<--ultra>：解锁 20 以上（最高 22）的高压缩级别，这会使用多得多的内存。请注"
"意，使用这些级别时，解压缩也将需要更多内存。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:109
msgid ""
"B<--fast[=#]>: switch to ultra-fast compression levels. If B<=#> is not "
"present, it defaults to B<1>. The higher the value, the faster the "
"compression speed, at the cost of some compression ratio. This setting "
"overwrites compression level if one was set previously. Similarly, if a "
"compression level is set after B<--fast>, it overrides it."
msgstr ""
"B<--fast[=#]>：切换到超快压缩级别。如果没有给出 B<=#>，则默认为 B<1>。数值越"
"大，压缩速度越快，但会牺牲一定的压缩率。如果先前设置过压缩级别，此设置会将其"
"覆盖。类似地，如果在 B<--fast> 之后设置了压缩级别，则会覆盖此设置。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:112
msgid ""
"B<-T#>, B<--threads=#>: Compress using B<#> working threads (default: "
"between 1 and 4 depending on physical CPU cores; see B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS> "
"below). If B<#> is 0, attempt to detect and use the number of physical CPU "
"cores. In all cases, the nb of threads is capped to B<ZSTDMT_NBWORKERS_MAX>, "
"which is either 64 in 32-bit mode, or 256 for 64-bit environments. This "
"modifier does nothing if B<zstd> is compiled without multithread support."
msgstr ""
"B<-T#>, B<--threads=#>：使用 B<#> 个工作线程进行压缩（默认值：根据物理 CPU 核"
"心数在 1 到 4 之间；参见下方的 B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS>）。如果 B<#> 为 0，则尝试检"
"测并使用物理 CPU 核心的数量。在所有情况下，线程数都会被限制在 "
"B<ZSTDMT_NBWORKERS_MAX> 以内，该值在 32 位模式下为 64，在 64 位环境下为 256。"
"如果编译 B<zstd> 时未启用多线程支持，则此修饰符不起作用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:115
msgid ""
"B<--single-thread>: Use a single thread for both I/O and compression. As "
"compression is serialized with I/O, this can be slightly slower. Single-"
"thread mode features significantly lower memory usage, which can be useful "
"for systems with limited amount of memory, such as 32-bit systems."
msgstr ""
"B<--single-thread>：使用单个线程同时处理 I/O 和压缩。由于压缩与 I/O 是串行进"
"行的，这可能会稍慢一些。单线程模式的内存占用显著更低，这对于内存有限的系统"
"（例如 32 位系统）可能很有用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:118
msgid ""
"Note 1: this mode is the only available one when multithread support is "
"disabled."
msgstr "注 1：当禁用多线程支持时，这是唯一可用的模式。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:121
msgid ""
"Note 2: this mode is different from B<-T1>, which spawns 1 compression "
"thread in parallel with I/O. Final compressed result is also slightly "
"different from B<-T1>."
msgstr ""
"注 2：此模式不同于 B<-T1>，后者会派生 1 个与 I/O 并行的压缩线程。最终的压缩结"
"果也与 B<-T1> 略有不同。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:124
msgid ""
"B<--auto-threads={physical,logical} (default: physical)>: When using a "
"default amount of threads via B<-T0>, choose the default based on the number "
"of detected physical or logical cores."
msgstr ""
"B<--auto-threads={physical,logical} (default: physical)>：当通过 B<-T0> 使用"
"默认线程数时，根据检测到的物理或逻辑核心数量来选择默认值。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:127
msgid ""
"B<--adapt[=min=#,max=#]>: B<zstd> will dynamically adapt compression level "
"to perceived I/O conditions. Compression level adaptation can be observed "
"live by using command B<-v>. Adaptation can be constrained between supplied "
"B<min> and B<max> levels. The feature works when combined with multi-"
"threading and B<--long> mode. It does not work with B<--single-thread>. It "
"sets window size to 8 MiB by default (can be changed manually, see B<wlog>). "
"Due to the chaotic nature of dynamic adaptation, compressed result is not "
"reproducible."
msgstr ""
"B<--adapt[=min=#,max=#]>：B<zstd> 会根据感知到的 I/O 状况动态调整压缩级别。可"
"以使用 B<-v> 命令实时观察压缩级别的自适应过程。自适应可以被约束在所提供的 "
"B<min> 和 B<max> 级别之间。该特性在与多线程以及 B<--long> 模式结合使用时有"
"效。它不适用于 B<--single-thread>。它默认将窗口大小设置为 8 MiB（可手动更改，"
"参见 B<wlog>）。由于动态自适应具有混沌特性，压缩结果不可复现。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:130
msgid ""
"I<Note>: at the time of this writing, B<--adapt> can remain stuck at low "
"speed when combined with multiple worker threads (E<gt>=2)."
msgstr ""
"I<注>：在撰写本文时，B<--adapt> 与多个工作线程（E<gt>=2）结合使用时，可能会一"
"直停留在低速状态。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:133
msgid ""
"B<--long[=#]>: enables long distance matching with B<#> B<windowLog>, if "
"B<#> is not present it defaults to B<27>. This increases the window size "
"(B<windowLog>) and memory usage for both the compressor and decompressor. "
"This setting is designed to improve the compression ratio for files with "
"long matches at a large distance."
msgstr ""
"B<--long[=#]>：启用长距离匹配，其 B<windowLog> 为 B<#>；如果没有给出 B<#>，则"
"默认为 B<27>。这会增大窗口大小（B<windowLog>）以及压缩器和解压缩器的内存占"
"用。此设置旨在提高那些在较大距离上存在长匹配的文件的压缩率。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:136 raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:298
msgid ""
"Note: If B<windowLog> is set to larger than 27, B<--long=windowLog> or B<--"
"memory=windowSize> needs to be passed to the decompressor."
msgstr ""
"注意：如果 B<windowLog> 设置为大于 27，则需要向解压缩器传递 B<--"
"long=windowLog> 或 B<--memory=windowSize>。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:139
msgid ""
"B<--max>: set advanced parameters to maximum compression. warning: this "
"setting is very slow and uses a lot of resources. It\\'s inappropriate for "
"32-bit mode and therefore disabled in this mode."
msgstr ""
"B<--max>：将高级参数设置为最大压缩。警告：此设置非常慢，并且会占用大量资源。"
"它不适用于 32 位模式，因此在该模式下被禁用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:142
msgid "B<-D DICT>: use B<DICT> as Dictionary to compress or decompress FILE(s)"
msgstr "B<-D DICT>：使用 B<DICT> 作为字典来压缩或解压缩文件"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:145
msgid ""
"B<--patch-from FILE>: Specify the file to be used as a reference point for "
"zstd\\'s diff engine. This is effectively dictionary compression with some "
"convenient parameter selection, namely that I<windowSize> E<gt> I<srcSize>."
msgstr ""
"B<--patch-from FILE>：指定要用作 zstd 差分引擎参考点的文件。这实际上就是字典"
"压缩，只是采用了一些方便的参数选择，即 I<windowSize> E<gt> I<srcSize>。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:148
msgid "Note: cannot use both this and B<-D> together."
msgstr "注意：不能同时使用此选项和 B<-D>。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:151
msgid ""
"Note: B<--long> mode will be automatically activated if I<chainLog> E<lt> "
"I<fileLog> (I<fileLog> being the I<windowLog> required to cover the whole "
"file). You can also manually force it."
msgstr ""
"注意：如果 I<chainLog> E<lt> I<fileLog>（I<fileLog> 即覆盖整个文件所需的 "
"I<windowLog>），则会自动激活 B<--long> 模式。你也可以手动强制启用它。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:154
msgid ""
"Note: up to level 15, you can use B<--patch-from> in B<--single-thread> mode "
"to improve compression ratio marginally at the cost of speed. Using \\'--"
"single-thread\\' above level 15 will lead to lower compression ratios."
msgstr ""
"注意：在不超过 15 级的情况下，你可以在 B<--single-thread> 模式下使用 B<--"
"patch-from>，以速度为代价略微提高压缩率。在 15 级以上使用 “--single-thread” "
"会导致更低的压缩率。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:157
msgid ""
"Note: for level 19, you can get increased compression ratio at the cost of "
"speed by specifying B<--zstd=targetLength=> to be something large (i.e. "
"4096), and by setting a large B<--zstd=chainLog=>."
msgstr ""
"注意：对于 19 级，你可以通过将 B<--zstd=targetLength=> 指定为较大的值（例如 "
"4096），并设置较大的 B<--zstd=chainLog=>，以速度为代价来提高压缩率。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:160
msgid ""
"B<--rsyncable>: B<zstd> will periodically synchronize the compression state "
"to make the compressed file more rsync-friendly. There is a negligible "
"impact to compression ratio, and a potential impact to compression speed, "
"perceptible at higher speeds, for example when combining B<--rsyncable> with "
"many parallel worker threads. This feature does not work with B<--single-"
"thread>. You probably don\\'t want to use it with long range mode, since it "
"will decrease the effectiveness of the synchronization points, but your "
"mileage may vary."
msgstr ""
"B<--rsyncable>：B<zstd> 会定期同步压缩状态，以使压缩文件对 rsync 更友好。这对"
"压缩率的影响可以忽略不计，但可能会影响压缩速度，在较高速度下会较为明显，例如"
"当 B<--rsyncable> 与许多并行工作线程结合使用时。此特性不适用于 B<--single-"
"thread>。你或许不会想在长距离模式下使用它，因为这会降低同步点的效果，不过实际"
"情况可能因人而异。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:163
msgid ""
"B<-C>, B<--[no-]check>: add integrity check computed from uncompressed data "
"(default: enabled)"
msgstr ""
"B<-C>, B<--[no-]check>：添加根据未压缩数据计算得出的完整性校验（默认值：启"
"用）"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:166
msgid ""
"B<--[no-]content-size>: enable / disable whether or not the original size of "
"the file is placed in the header of the compressed file. The default option "
"is B<--content-size> (meaning that the original size will be placed in the "
"header)."
msgstr ""
"B<--[no-]content-size>：启用/禁用是否将文件的原始大小放入压缩文件的头部。默认"
"选项为 B<--content-size>（意味着原始大小将被放入头部）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:169
msgid ""
"B<--no-dictID>: do not store dictionary ID within frame header (dictionary "
"compression). The decoder will have to rely on implicit knowledge about "
"which dictionary to use, it won\\'t be able to check if it\\'s correct."
msgstr ""
"B<--no-dictID>：不在帧头部中存储字典 ID（字典压缩）。解码器将不得不依赖关于使"
"用哪个字典的隐式知识，而无法检查其是否正确。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:172
msgid ""
"B<-M#>, B<--memory=#>: Set a memory usage limit. By default, B<zstd> uses "
"128 MiB for decompression as the maximum amount of memory the decompressor "
"is allowed to use, but you can override this manually if need be in either "
"direction (i.e. you can increase or decrease it)."
msgstr ""
"B<-M#>, B<--memory=#>：设置内存使用上限。默认情况下，B<zstd> 将 128 MiB 作为"
"解压缩器允许使用的最大内存量，但如有需要，你可以手动在任一方向上覆盖此值（即"
"可以增大或减小它）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:175
msgid ""
"This is also used during compression when using with B<--patch-from=>. In "
"this case, this parameter overrides that maximum size allowed for a "
"dictionary. (128 MiB)."
msgstr ""
"在与 B<--patch-from=> 一起使用进行压缩时，也会用到此值。在这种情况下，此参数"
"会覆盖字典所允许的最大大小（128 MiB）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:178
msgid ""
"Additionally, this can be used to limit memory for dictionary training. This "
"parameter overrides the default limit of 2 GiB. zstd will load training "
"samples up to the memory limit and ignore the rest."
msgstr ""
"此外，这还可用于限制字典训练所用的内存。此参数会覆盖默认的 2 GiB 限制。zstd "
"将加载训练样本直到达到内存上限，并忽略其余部分。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:181
msgid ""
"B<--stream-size=#>: Sets the pledged source size of input coming from a "
"stream. This value must be exact, as it will be included in the produced "
"frame header. Incorrect stream sizes will cause an error. This information "
"will be used to better optimize compression parameters, resulting in better "
"and potentially faster compression, especially for smaller source sizes."
msgstr ""
"B<--stream-size=#>：设置来自流的输入所承诺的源大小。此值必须精确，因为它将被"
"包含在生成的帧头部中。不正确的流大小会导致错误。此信息将用于更好地优化压缩参"
"数，从而带来更好且可能更快的压缩，尤其是对于较小的源大小。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:184
msgid ""
"B<--size-hint=#>: When handling input from a stream, B<zstd> must guess how "
"large the source size will be when optimizing compression parameters. If the "
"stream size is relatively small, this guess may be a poor one, resulting in "
"a higher compression ratio than expected. This feature allows for "
"controlling the guess when needed. Exact guesses result in better "
"compression ratios. Overestimates result in slightly degraded compression "
"ratios, while underestimates may result in significant degradation."
msgstr ""
"B<--size-hint=#>：在处理来自流的输入时，B<zstd> 在优化压缩参数时必须猜测源大"
"小会有多大。如果流的大小相对较小，这一猜测可能不准确，从而导致压缩率高于预"
"期。此特性允许在需要时控制该猜测值。精确的猜测会带来更好的压缩率。高估会导致"
"压缩率略有下降，而低估则可能导致显著下降。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:187
msgid ""
"B<--target-compressed-block-size=#>: Attempt to produce compressed blocks of "
"approximately this size. This will split larger blocks in order to approach "
"this target. This feature is notably useful for improved latency, when the "
"receiver can leverage receiving early incomplete data. This parameter "
"defines a loose target: compressed blocks will target this size \"on "
"average\", but individual blocks can still be larger or smaller. Enabling "
"this feature can decrease compression speed by up to ~10% at level 1. Higher "
"levels will see smaller relative speed regression, becoming invisible at "
"higher settings."
msgstr ""
"B<--target-compressed-block-size=#>：尝试生成大约为此大小的压缩块。为了接近此"
"目标，较大的块会被拆分。当接收方能够利用提前收到的不完整数据时，此特性对于改"
"善延迟尤其有用。此参数定义的是一个宽松的目标：压缩块会以“平均”达到此大小为目"
"标，但各个块仍可能更大或更小。启用此特性在 1 级时最多可使压缩速度降低约 10%。"
"级别越高，相对速度的下降越小，在更高的设置下则难以察觉。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:190
msgid ""
"B<-f>, B<--force>: disable input and output checks. Allows overwriting "
"existing files, input from console, output to stdout, operating on links, "
"block devices, etc. During decompression and when the output destination is "
"stdout, pass-through unrecognized formats as-is."
msgstr ""
"B<-f>, B<--force>：禁用输入和输出检查。允许覆盖现有文件、从控制台输入、输出"
"到 stdout、对链接和块设备等进行操作。在解压缩过程中且输出目标为 stdout 时，将"
"无法识别的格式原样透传。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:193
msgid ""
"B<-c>, B<--stdout>: write to standard output (even if it is the console); "
"keep original files (disable B<--rm>)."
msgstr ""
"B<-c>, B<--stdout>：写入标准输出（即使它是控制台）；保留原始文件（禁用 B<--"
"rm>）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:196
msgid ""
"B<-o FILE>: save result into B<FILE>. Note that this operation is in "
"conflict with B<-c>. If both operations are present on the command line, the "
"last expressed one wins."
msgstr ""
"B<-o FILE>：将结果保存到 B<FILE>。请注意，此操作与 B<-c> 冲突。如果命令行中同"
"时出现这两个操作，则以最后给出的为准。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:199
msgid ""
"B<--[no-]sparse>: enable / disable sparse FS support, to make files with "
"many zeroes smaller on disk. Creating sparse files may save disk space and "
"speed up decompression by reducing the amount of disk I/O. default: enabled "
"when output is into a file, and disabled when output is stdout. This setting "
"overrides default and can force sparse mode over stdout."
msgstr ""
"B<--[no-]sparse>：启用/禁用稀疏文件系统支持，以使含有大量零字节的文件在磁盘上"
"占用更小的空间。创建稀疏文件可以节省磁盘空间，并通过减少磁盘 I/O 量来加快解压"
"缩。默认值：当输出到文件时启用，当输出为 stdout 时禁用。此设置会覆盖默认值，"
"并可强制在 stdout 上使用稀疏模式。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:202
msgid ""
"B<--[no-]pass-through> enable / disable passing through uncompressed files "
"as-is. During decompression when pass-through is enabled, unrecognized "
"formats will be copied as-is from the input to the output. By default, pass-"
"through will occur when the output destination is stdout and the force (B<-"
"f>) option is set."
msgstr ""
"B<--[no-]pass-through>：启用/禁用将未压缩文件原样透传。在解压缩过程中启用透传"
"时，无法识别的格式将从输入原样复制到输出。默认情况下，当输出目标为 stdout 且"
"设置了强制（B<-f>）选项时，会进行透传。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:205
msgid ""
"B<--rm>: remove source file(s) after successful compression or "
"decompression. This command is silently ignored if output is B<stdout>. If "
"used in combination with B<-o>, triggers a confirmation prompt (which can be "
"silenced with B<-f>), as this is a destructive operation."
msgstr ""
"B<--rm>：在压缩或解压缩成功后删除源文件。如果输出为 B<stdout>，此命令会被静默"
"忽略。如果与 B<-o> 结合使用，由于这是一项破坏性操作，会触发确认提示（可用 B<-"
"f> 使其静默）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:208
msgid ""
"B<-k>, B<--keep>: keep source file(s) after successful compression or "
"decompression. This is the default behavior."
msgstr "B<-k>, B<--keep>：在压缩或解压缩成功后保留源文件。这是默认行为。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:211
msgid ""
"B<-r>: operate recursively on directories. It selects all files in the named "
"directory and all its subdirectories. This can be useful both to reduce "
"command line typing, and to circumvent shell expansion limitations, when "
"there are a lot of files and naming breaks the maximum size of a command "
"line."
msgstr ""
"B<-r>：对目录进行递归操作。它会选中指定目录及其所有子目录中的全部文件。当文件"
"很多且文件名会超出命令行的最大长度时，这既有助于减少命令行输入，也可以规避 "
"shell 展开的限制。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:214
msgid ""
"B<--filelist FILE> read a list of files to process as content from B<FILE>. "
"Format is compatible with B<ls> output, with one file per line."
msgstr ""
"B<--filelist FILE>：从 B<FILE> 中读取要处理的文件列表作为内容。其格式与 "
"B<ls> 的输出兼容，每行一个文件。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:217
msgid ""
"B<--output-dir-flat DIR>: resulting files are stored into target B<DIR> "
"directory, instead of same directory as origin file. Be aware that this "
"command can introduce name collision issues, if multiple files, from "
"different directories, end up having the same name. Collision resolution "
"ensures first file with a given name will be present in B<DIR>, while in "
"combination with B<-f>, the last file will be present instead."
msgstr ""
"B<--output-dir-flat DIR>：生成的文件会被存储到目标 B<DIR> 目录中，而不是与源"
"文件相同的目录。请注意，如果来自不同目录的多个文件最终具有相同的名称，此命令"
"可能会引入命名冲突问题。冲突解决机制会确保具有某一名称的第一个文件出现在 "
"B<DIR> 中，而在与 B<-f> 结合使用时，则会改为保留最后一个文件。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:220
msgid ""
"B<--output-dir-mirror DIR>: similar to B<--output-dir-flat>, the output "
"files are stored underneath target B<DIR> directory, but this option will "
"replicate input directory hierarchy into output B<DIR>."
msgstr ""
"B<--output-dir-mirror DIR>：与 B<--output-dir-flat> 类似，输出文件会被存储在"
"目标 B<DIR> 目录之下，但此选项会将输入的目录层次结构复制到输出的 B<DIR> 中。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:223
msgid ""
"If input directory contains \"..\", the files in this directory will be "
"ignored. If input directory is an absolute directory (i.e. \"/var/tmp/"
"abc\"), it will be stored into the \"output-dir/var/tmp/abc\". If there are "
"multiple input files or directories, name collision resolution will follow "
"the same rules as B<--output-dir-flat>."
msgstr ""
"如果输入目录包含 “..”，则该目录中的文件将被忽略。如果输入目录是绝对目录（例"
"如 “/var/tmp/abc”），它将被存储到 “output-dir/var/tmp/abc” 中。如果有多个输入"
"文件或目录，命名冲突的解决将遵循与 B<--output-dir-flat> 相同的规则。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:226
msgid ""
"B<--format=FORMAT>: compress and decompress in other formats. If compiled "
"with support, zstd can compress to or decompress from other compression "
"algorithm formats. Possibly available options are B<zstd>, B<gzip>, B<xz>, "
"B<lzma>, and B<lz4>. If no such format is provided, B<zstd> is the default."
msgstr ""
"B<--format=FORMAT>：以其他格式进行压缩和解压缩。如果编译时启用了相应支持，"
"zstd 可以压缩为其他压缩算法格式，或从中解压缩。可能可用的选项有 B<zstd>、"
"B<gzip>、B<xz>、B<lzma> 和 B<lz4>。如果未提供此类格式，则默认为 B<zstd>。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:229
msgid "B<-h>/B<-H>, B<--help>: display help/long help and exit"
msgstr "B<-h>/B<-H>, B<--help>：显示帮助/详细帮助并退出"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:232
msgid ""
"B<-V>, B<--version>: display version number and immediately exit. note that, "
"since it exits, flags specified after B<-V> are effectively ignored. "
"Advanced: B<-vV> also displays supported formats. B<-vvV> also displays "
"POSIX support. B<-qV> will only display the version number, suitable for "
"machine reading."
msgstr ""
"B<-V>, B<--version>：显示版本号并立即退出。请注意，由于它会退出，在 B<-V> 之"
"后指定的标志实际上会被忽略。高级用法：B<-vV> 还会显示所支持的格式。B<-vvV> 还"
"会显示 POSIX 支持情况。B<-qV> 将只显示版本号，适合机器读取。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:235
msgid "B<-v>, B<--verbose>: verbose mode, display more information"
msgstr "B<-v>, B<--verbose>：详细模式，显示更多信息"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:238
msgid ""
"B<-q>, B<--quiet>: suppress warnings, interactivity, and notifications. "
"specify twice to suppress errors too."
msgstr "B<-q>, B<--quiet>：抑制警告、交互和通知。指定两次也会抑制错误。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:241
msgid ""
"B<--no-progress>: do not display the progress bar, but keep all other "
"messages."
msgstr "B<--no-progress>：不显示进度条，但保留所有其他消息。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:244
msgid ""
"B<--show-default-cparams>: shows the default compression parameters that "
"will be used for a particular input file, based on the provided compression "
"level and the input size. If the provided file is not a regular file (e.g. a "
"pipe), this flag will output the parameters used for inputs of unknown size."
msgstr ""
"B<--show-default-cparams>：根据所提供的压缩级别和输入大小，显示将用于某个特定"
"输入文件的默认压缩参数。如果所提供的文件不是普通文件（例如管道），此标志将输"
"出用于未知大小输入的参数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:247
msgid ""
"B<--exclude-compressed>: only compress files that are not already compressed."
msgstr "B<--exclude-compressed>：仅压缩尚未被压缩的文件。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:250
msgid "B<-->: All arguments after B<--> are treated as files"
msgstr "B<-->：B<--> 之后的所有参数都被视为文件"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:253
#, no-wrap
msgid "gzip Operation Modifiers"
msgstr "gzip 操作修饰符"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:255
msgid ""
"When invoked via a B<gzip> symlink, B<zstd> will support further options "
"that intend to mimic the B<gzip> behavior:"
msgstr ""
"在经由 B<gzip> 符号链接调用时，B<zstd> 将支持以下额外的选项来模拟 B<gzip> 的"
"行为："

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-n>, B<--no-name>"
msgstr "B<-n>, B<--no-name>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:259
msgid ""
"do not store the original filename and timestamps when compressing a file. "
"This is the default behavior and hence a no-op."
msgstr ""
"压缩文件时不要保存原始文件名和时间戳。这是默认选项，因此不会改变程序行为。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:260
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<--best>"
msgstr "B<--best>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:263
msgid "alias to the option B<-9>."
msgstr "是 B<-9> 选项的别名。"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:264
#, no-wrap
msgid "Environment Variables"
msgstr "环境变量"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:266
msgid ""
"Employing environment variables to set parameters has security implications. "
"Therefore, this avenue is intentionally limited. Only B<ZSTD_CLEVEL> and "
"B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS> are currently supported. They set the default compression "
"level and number of threads to use during compression, respectively."
msgstr ""
"使用环境变量来设置参数会带来安全方面的影响。因此，这一途径被有意加以限制。目"
"前仅支持 B<ZSTD_CLEVEL> 和 B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS>。它们分别设置压缩时使用的默认压"
"缩级别和线程数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:269
msgid ""
"B<ZSTD_CLEVEL> can be used to set the level between 1 and 19 (the \"normal\" "
"range). If the value of B<ZSTD_CLEVEL> is not a valid integer, it will be "
"ignored with a warning message. B<ZSTD_CLEVEL> just replaces the default "
"compression level (B<3>)."
msgstr ""
"B<ZSTD_CLEVEL> 可用于设置 1 到 19 之间（即“正常”范围）的级别。如果 "
"B<ZSTD_CLEVEL> 的值不是有效的整数，它将被忽略并给出一条警告消息。"
"B<ZSTD_CLEVEL> 只是替换默认的压缩级别（B<3>）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:272
msgid ""
"B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS> can be used to set the number of threads B<zstd> will "
"attempt to use during compression. If the value of B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS> is not "
"a valid unsigned integer, it will be ignored with a warning message. "
"B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS> has a default value of B<max(1, min(4, nbCores/4))>, and "
"is capped at ZSTDMT_NBWORKERS_MAX==200. B<zstd> must be compiled with "
"multithread support for this variable to have any effect."
msgstr ""
"B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS> 可用于设置 B<zstd> 在压缩时将尝试使用的线程数。如果 "
"B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS> 的值不是有效的无符号整数，它将被忽略并给出一条警告消息。"
"B<ZSTD_NBTHREADS> 的默认值为 B<max(1, min(4, nbCores/4))>，且上限为 "
"ZSTDMT_NBWORKERS_MAX==200。必须在编译 B<zstd> 时启用多线程支持，此变量才会产"
"生任何效果。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:275
msgid ""
"They can both be overridden by corresponding command line arguments: B<-#> "
"for compression level and B<-T#> for number of compression threads."
msgstr ""
"这两者都可以被相应的命令行参数覆盖：B<-#> 用于压缩级别，B<-T#> 用于压缩线程"
"数。"

#. type: SH
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:276
#, no-wrap
msgid "ADVANCED COMPRESSION OPTIONS"
msgstr "高级压缩选项"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:278
msgid ""
"B<zstd> provides 22 predefined regular compression levels plus the fast "
"levels. A compression level is translated internally into multiple advanced "
"parameters that control the behavior of the compressor (one can observe the "
"result of this translation with B<--show-default-cparams>). These advanced "
"parameters can be overridden using advanced compression options."
msgstr ""
"B<zstd> 提供 22 个预定义的常规压缩级别以及快速级别。在内部，压缩级别会被转换"
"为多个控制压缩器行为的高级参数（可以用 B<--show-default-cparams> 观察这一转换"
"的结果）。这些高级参数可以使用高级压缩选项来覆盖。"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:279
#, no-wrap
msgid "--zstd[=options]:"
msgstr "--zstd[=options]:"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:281
msgid ""
"The I<options> are provided as a comma-separated list. You may specify only "
"the options you want to change and the rest will be taken from the selected "
"or default compression level. The list of available I<options>:"
msgstr ""
"I<options> 以逗号分隔的列表形式提供。你可以只指定想要更改的选项，其余的将取自"
"所选的或默认的压缩级别。可用 I<options> 的列表如下："

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:282
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<strategy>=I<strat>, B<strat>=I<strat>"
msgstr "B<strategy>=I<strat>, B<strat>=I<strat>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:285
msgid "Specify a strategy used by a match finder."
msgstr "指定匹配查找器所使用的策略。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:288
msgid ""
"There are 9 strategies numbered from 1 to 9, from fastest to strongest: "
"1=B<ZSTD_fast>, 2=B<ZSTD_dfast>, 3=B<ZSTD_greedy>, 4=B<ZSTD_lazy>, "
"5=B<ZSTD_lazy2>, 6=B<ZSTD_btlazy2>, 7=B<ZSTD_btopt>, 8=B<ZSTD_btultra>, "
"9=B<ZSTD_btultra2>."
msgstr ""
"共有 9 种策略，编号从 1 到 9，从最快到最强：1=B<ZSTD_fast>, 2=B<ZSTD_dfast>, "
"3=B<ZSTD_greedy>, 4=B<ZSTD_lazy>, 5=B<ZSTD_lazy2>, 6=B<ZSTD_btlazy2>, "
"7=B<ZSTD_btopt>, 8=B<ZSTD_btultra>, 9=B<ZSTD_btultra2>。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:289
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<windowLog>=I<wlog>, B<wlog>=I<wlog>"
msgstr "B<windowLog>=I<wlog>, B<wlog>=I<wlog>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:292
msgid "Specify the maximum number of bits for a match distance."
msgstr "指定匹配距离的最大位数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:295
msgid ""
"The higher number of increases the chance to find a match which usually "
"improves compression ratio. It also increases memory requirements for the "
"compressor and decompressor. The minimum I<wlog> is 10 (1 KiB) and the "
"maximum is 30 (1 GiB) on 32-bit platforms and 31 (2 GiB) on 64-bit platforms."
msgstr ""
"该值越大，找到匹配的机会就越大，这通常会提高压缩率。它也会增加压缩器和解压缩"
"器的内存需求。I<wlog> 的最小值为 10（1 KiB），最大值在 32 位平台上为 30（1 "
"GiB），在 64 位平台上为 31（2 GiB）。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<hashLog>=I<hlog>, B<hlog>=I<hlog>"
msgstr "B<hashLog>=I<hlog>, B<hlog>=I<hlog>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:302
msgid "Specify the maximum number of bits for a hash table."
msgstr "指定哈希表的最大位数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:305
msgid ""
"Bigger hash tables cause fewer collisions which usually makes compression "
"faster, but requires more memory during compression."
msgstr ""
"更大的哈希表会减少冲突，这通常会使压缩更快，但在压缩过程中需要更多内存。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:308
msgid ""
"The minimum I<hlog> is 6 (64 entries / 256 B) and the maximum is 30 (1B "
"entries / 4 GiB)."
msgstr ""
"I<hlog> 的最小值为 6（64 个条目 / 256 B），最大值为 30（10 亿个条目 / 4 "
"GiB）。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<chainLog>=I<clog>, B<clog>=I<clog>"
msgstr "B<chainLog>=I<clog>, B<clog>=I<clog>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:312
msgid ""
"Specify the maximum number of bits for the secondary search structure, whose "
"form depends on the selected B<strategy>."
msgstr "指定次级搜索结构的最大位数，其形式取决于所选的 B<strategy>。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:315
msgid ""
"Higher numbers of bits increases the chance to find a match which usually "
"improves compression ratio. It also slows down compression speed and "
"increases memory requirements for compression. This option is ignored for "
"the B<ZSTD_fast> B<strategy>, which only has the primary hash table."
msgstr ""
"位数越多，找到匹配的机会就越大，这通常会提高压缩率。它也会降低压缩速度并增加"
"压缩的内存需求。对于只有主哈希表的 B<ZSTD_fast> B<strategy>，此选项会被忽略。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:318
msgid ""
"The minimum I<clog> is 6 (64 entries / 256 B) and the maximum is 29 (512M "
"entries / 2 GiB) on 32-bit platforms and 30 (1B entries / 4 GiB) on 64-bit "
"platforms."
msgstr ""
"I<clog> 的最小值为 6（64 个条目 / 256 B），最大值在 32 位平台上为 29（5.12 亿"
"个条目 / 2 GiB），在 64 位平台上为 30（10 亿个条目 / 4 GiB）。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:319
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<searchLog>=I<slog>, B<slog>=I<slog>"
msgstr "B<searchLog>=I<slog>, B<slog>=I<slog>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:322
msgid ""
"Specify the maximum number of searches in a hash chain or a binary tree "
"using logarithmic scale."
msgstr "以对数刻度指定在哈希链或二叉树中的最大搜索次数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:325
msgid ""
"More searches increases the chance to find a match which usually increases "
"compression ratio but decreases compression speed."
msgstr "更多的搜索会增大找到匹配的机会，这通常会提高压缩率但会降低压缩速度。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:328
msgid "The minimum I<slog> is 1 and the maximum is \\'windowLog\\' - 1."
msgstr "I<slog> 的最小值为 1，最大值为 “windowLog” - 1。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:329
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<minMatch>=I<mml>, B<mml>=I<mml>"
msgstr "B<minMatch>=I<mml>, B<mml>=I<mml>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:332
msgid "Specify the minimum searched length of a match in a hash table."
msgstr "指定在哈希表中匹配的最小搜索长度。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:335
msgid ""
"Larger search lengths usually decrease compression ratio but improve "
"decompression speed."
msgstr "更大的搜索长度通常会降低压缩率，但会提高解压缩速度。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:338
msgid "The minimum I<mml> is 3 and the maximum is 7."
msgstr "I<mml> 的最小值为 3，最大值为 7。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:339
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<targetLength>=I<tlen>, B<tlen>=I<tlen>"
msgstr "B<targetLength>=I<tlen>, B<tlen>=I<tlen>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:342
msgid "The impact of this field vary depending on selected strategy."
msgstr "此字段的影响因所选策略而异。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:345
msgid ""
"For B<ZSTD_btopt>, B<ZSTD_btultra> and B<ZSTD_btultra2>, it specifies the "
"minimum match length that causes match finder to stop searching. A larger "
"B<targetLength> usually improves compression ratio but decreases compression "
"speed."
msgstr ""
"对于 B<ZSTD_btopt>、B<ZSTD_btultra> 和 B<ZSTD_btultra2>，它指定使匹配查找器停"
"止搜索的最小匹配长度。更大的 B<targetLength> 通常会提高压缩率但会降低压缩速"
"度。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:348
msgid ""
"For B<ZSTD_fast>, it triggers ultra-fast mode when E<gt> 0. The value "
"represents the amount of data skipped between match sampling. Impact is "
"reversed: a larger B<targetLength> increases compression speed but decreases "
"compression ratio."
msgstr ""
"对于 B<ZSTD_fast>，当其 E<gt> 0 时会触发超快模式。该值表示在匹配采样之间跳过"
"的数据量。其影响是相反的：更大的 B<targetLength> 会提高压缩速度但会降低压缩"
"率。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:351
msgid "For all other strategies, this field has no impact."
msgstr "对于所有其他策略，此字段没有影响。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:354
msgid "The minimum I<tlen> is 0 and the maximum is 128 KiB."
msgstr "I<tlen> 的最小值为 0，最大值为 128 KiB。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:355
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<overlapLog>=I<ovlog>, B<ovlog>=I<ovlog>"
msgstr "B<overlapLog>=I<ovlog>, B<ovlog>=I<ovlog>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:358
msgid ""
"Determine B<overlapSize>, amount of data reloaded from previous job. This "
"parameter is only available when multithreading is enabled. Reloading more "
"data improves compression ratio, but decreases speed."
msgstr ""
"确定 B<overlapSize>，即从上一个任务重新加载的数据量。此参数仅在启用多线程时可"
"用。重新加载更多数据会提高压缩率，但会降低速度。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:361
msgid ""
"The minimum I<ovlog> is 0, and the maximum is 9. 1 means \"no overlap\", "
"hence completely independent jobs. 9 means \"full overlap\", meaning up to "
"B<windowSize> is reloaded from previous job. Reducing I<ovlog> by 1 reduces "
"the reloaded amount by a factor 2. For example, 8 means \"windowSize/2\", "
"and 6 means \"windowSize/8\". Value 0 is special and means \"default\": "
"I<ovlog> is automatically determined by B<zstd>. In which case, I<ovlog> "
"will range from 6 to 9, depending on selected I<strat>."
msgstr ""
"I<ovlog> 的最小值为 0，最大值为 9。1 表示“无重叠”，因此任务之间完全独立。9 表"
"示“完全重叠”，即从上一个任务最多重新加载 B<windowSize> 大小的数据。将 "
"I<ovlog> 减小 1 会使重新加载的数据量减少为原来的一半。例如，8 表"
"示“windowSize/2”，6 表示“windowSize/8”。值 0 比较特殊，表示“默认”：I<ovlog> "
"由 B<zstd> 自动确定。在这种情况下，I<ovlog> 的取值将在 6 到 9 之间，具体取决"
"于所选的 I<strat>。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<ldmHashRateLog>=I<lhrlog>, B<lhrlog>=I<lhrlog>"
msgstr "B<ldmHashRateLog>=I<lhrlog>, B<lhrlog>=I<lhrlog>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:365
msgid ""
"Specify the frequency of inserting entries into the long distance matching "
"hash table."
msgstr "指定向长距离匹配哈希表中插入条目的频率。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:368 raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:381 raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:394
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:407
msgid "This option is ignored unless long distance matching is enabled."
msgstr "除非启用了长距离匹配，否则此选项会被忽略。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:371
msgid ""
"Larger values will improve compression speed. Deviating far from the default "
"value will likely result in a decrease in compression ratio."
msgstr "更大的值将提高压缩速度。与默认值偏离太远很可能会导致压缩率下降。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:374
msgid "The default value varies between 4 and 7, depending on B<strategy>."
msgstr "默认值在 4 到 7 之间变化，具体取决于 B<strategy>。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:375
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<ldmHashLog>=I<lhlog>, B<lhlog>=I<lhlog>"
msgstr "B<ldmHashLog>=I<lhlog>, B<lhlog>=I<lhlog>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:378
msgid ""
"Specify the maximum size for a hash table used for long distance matching."
msgstr "指定用于长距离匹配的哈希表的最大大小。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:384
msgid ""
"Bigger hash tables usually improve compression ratio at the expense of more "
"memory during compression and a decrease in compression speed."
msgstr ""
"更大的哈希表通常会提高压缩率，但代价是压缩过程中占用更多内存以及压缩速度下"
"降。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:387
msgid ""
"The minimum I<lhlog> is 6 and the maximum is 30 (default: B<windowLog - "
"ldmHashRateLog>)."
msgstr ""
"I<lhlog> 的最小值为 6，最大值为 30（默认值：B<windowLog - ldmHashRateLog>）。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:388
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<ldmMinMatch>=I<lmml>, B<lmml>=I<lmml>"
msgstr "B<ldmMinMatch>=I<lmml>, B<lmml>=I<lmml>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:391
msgid ""
"Specify the minimum searched length of a match for long distance matching."
msgstr "指定长距离匹配中匹配的最小搜索长度。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:397
msgid "Larger/very small values usually decrease compression ratio."
msgstr "过大或过小的值通常都会降低压缩率。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:400
msgid ""
"The minimum I<lmml> is 4 and the maximum is 4096 (default: 32 to 64, "
"depending on B<strategy>)."
msgstr ""
"I<lmml> 的最小值为 4，最大值为 4096（默认值：32 到 64，具体取决于 "
"B<strategy>）。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:401
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<ldmBucketSizeLog>=I<lblog>, B<lblog>=I<lblog>"
msgstr "B<ldmBucketSizeLog>=I<lblog>, B<lblog>=I<lblog>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:404
msgid ""
"Specify the size of each bucket for the hash table used for long distance "
"matching."
msgstr "指定用于长距离匹配的哈希表中每个桶的大小。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:410
msgid ""
"Larger bucket sizes improve collision resolution but decrease compression "
"speed."
msgstr "更大的桶大小会改善冲突解决，但会降低压缩速度。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:413
msgid ""
"The minimum I<lblog> is 1 and the maximum is 8 (default: 4 to 8, depending "
"on B<strategy>)."
msgstr ""
"I<lblog> 的最小值为 1，最大值为 8（默认值：4 到 8，具体取决于 B<strategy>）。"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:414
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example"
msgstr "示例"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:416
msgid ""
"The following parameters sets advanced compression options to something "
"similar to predefined level 19 for files bigger than 256 KB:"
msgstr ""
"对于大于 256 KB 的文件，以下参数会将高级压缩选项设置为类似于预定义的 19 级："

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:419
msgid "B<--zstd>=wlog=23,clog=23,hlog=22,slog=6,mml=3,tlen=48,strat=6"
msgstr "B<--zstd>=wlog=23,clog=23,hlog=22,slog=6,mml=3,tlen=48,strat=6"

#. type: SS
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:420
#, no-wrap
msgid "-B#:"
msgstr "-B#:"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:422
msgid ""
"Specify the size of each compression job. This parameter is only available "
"when multi-threading is enabled. Each compression job is run in parallel, so "
"this value indirectly impacts the nb of active threads. Default job size "
"varies depending on compression level (generally B<4 * windowSize>). B<-B#> "
"makes it possible to manually select a custom size. Note that job size must "
"respect a minimum value which is enforced transparently. This minimum is "
"either 512 KB, or B<overlapSize>, whichever is largest. Different job sizes "
"will lead to non-identical compressed frames."
msgstr ""
"指定每个压缩任务的大小。此参数仅在启用多线程时可用。每个压缩任务并行运行，因"
"此此值会间接影响活动线程的数量。默认任务大小因压缩级别而异（通常为 B<4 * "
"windowSize>）。B<-B#> 使得手动选择自定义大小成为可能。请注意，任务大小必须满"
"足一个透明强制执行的最小值。该最小值为 512 KB 或 B<overlapSize> 中的较大者。"
"不同的任务大小会导致不完全相同的压缩帧。"

#. type: SH
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:423
#, no-wrap
msgid "DICTIONARY BUILDER"
msgstr "字典构建器"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:425
msgid ""
"B<zstd> offers I<dictionary> compression, which greatly improves efficiency "
"on small files and messages. It\\'s possible to train B<zstd> with a set of "
"samples, the result of which is saved into a file called a B<dictionary>. "
"Then, during compression and decompression, reference the same dictionary, "
"using command B<-D dictionaryFileName>. Compression of small files similar "
"to the sample set will be greatly improved."
msgstr ""
"B<zstd> 提供 I<字典> 压缩，这可以大大提高对小文件和消息的压缩效率。可以用一组"
"样本来训练 B<zstd>，其结果会被保存到一个称为 B<dictionary>（字典）的文件中。"
"然后，在压缩和解压缩时，使用 B<-D dictionaryFileName> 命令引用同一个字典。对"
"与样本集相似的小文件的压缩将得到极大改善。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:426
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<--train FILEs>"
msgstr "B<--train FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:429
msgid ""
"Use FILEs as training set to create a dictionary. The training set should "
"ideally contain a lot of samples (E<gt> 100), and weight typically 100x the "
"target dictionary size (for example, ~10 MB for a 100 KB dictionary). B<--"
"train> can be combined with B<-r> to indicate a directory rather than "
"listing all the files, which can be useful to circumvent shell expansion "
"limits."
msgstr ""
"使用 FILEs 作为训练集来创建字典。理想情况下，训练集应包含大量样本（E<gt> 100 "
"个），且其总大小通常为目标字典大小的 100 倍（例如，对于 100 KB 的字典约为 10 "
"MB）。B<--train> 可以与 B<-r> 结合使用以指定一个目录，而不必列出所有文件，这"
"有助于规避 shell 展开的限制。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:432
msgid ""
"Since dictionary compression is mostly effective for small files, the "
"expectation is that the training set will only contain small files. In the "
"case where some samples happen to be large, only the first 128 KiB of these "
"samples will be used for training."
msgstr ""
"由于字典压缩主要对小文件有效，因此预期训练集只包含小文件。如果某些样本恰好很"
"大，则只有这些样本的前 128 KiB 会被用于训练。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:435
msgid ""
"B<--train> supports multithreading if B<zstd> is compiled with threading "
"support (default). Additional advanced parameters can be specified with B<--"
"train-fastcover>. The legacy dictionary builder can be accessed with B<--"
"train-legacy>. The slower cover dictionary builder can be accessed with B<--"
"train-cover>. Default B<--train> is equivalent to B<--train-"
"fastcover=d=8,steps=4>."
msgstr ""
"如果编译 B<zstd> 时启用了线程支持（默认），B<--train> 支持多线程。可以使用 "
"B<--train-fastcover> 指定额外的高级参数。可以通过 B<--train-legacy> 访问旧版"
"字典构建器。可以通过 B<--train-cover> 访问速度较慢的 cover 字典构建器。默认"
"的 B<--train> 等效于 B<--train-fastcover=d=8,steps=4>。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:436
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-o FILE>"
msgstr "B<-o FILE>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:439
msgid "Dictionary saved into B<FILE> (default name: dictionary)."
msgstr "字典将被保存到 B<FILE> 中（默认名称：dictionary）。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:440
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<--maxdict=#>"
msgstr "B<--maxdict=#>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:443
msgid ""
"Limit dictionary to specified size (default: 112640 bytes). As usual, "
"quantities are expressed in bytes by default, and it\\'s possible to employ "
"suffixes (like B<KB> or B<MB>) to specify larger values."
msgstr ""
"将字典限制为指定大小（默认值：112640 字节）。与通常一样，数量默认以字节表示，"
"并且可以使用后缀（如 B<KB> 或 B<MB>）来指定更大的值。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:444
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-#>"
msgstr "B<-#>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:447
msgid ""
"Use B<#> compression level during training (optional). Will generate "
"statistics more tuned for selected compression level, resulting in a "
"I<small> compression ratio improvement for this level."
msgstr ""
"在训练期间使用 B<#> 压缩级别（可选）。这将生成更针对所选压缩级别进行调优的统"
"计信息，从而使该级别的压缩率有 I<小幅> 提升。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:448
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-B#>"
msgstr "B<-B#>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:451
msgid "Split input files into blocks of size # (default: no split)"
msgstr "将输入文件拆分为大小为 # 的块（默认值：不拆分）"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:452
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<-M#>, B<--memory=#>"
msgstr "B<-M#>, B<--memory=#>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:455
msgid ""
"Limit the amount of sample data loaded for training (default: 2 GB). Note "
"that the default (2 GB) is also the maximum. This parameter can be useful in "
"situations where the training set size is not well controlled and could be "
"potentially very large. Since speed of the training process is directly "
"correlated to the size of the training sample set, a smaller sample set "
"leads to faster training."
msgstr ""
"限制为训练而加载的样本数据量（默认值：2 GB）。请注意，默认值（2 GB）同时也是"
"最大值。当训练集大小未得到良好控制且可能非常大时，此参数会很有用。由于训练过"
"程的速度与训练样本集的大小直接相关，因此较小的样本集会带来更快的训练。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:458
msgid ""
"In situations where the training set is larger than maximum memory, the CLI "
"will randomly select samples among the available ones, up to the maximum "
"allowed memory budget. This is meant to improve dictionary relevance by "
"mitigating the potential impact of clustering, such as selecting only files "
"from the beginning of a list sorted by modification date, or sorted by "
"alphabetical order. The randomization process is deterministic, so training "
"of the same list of files with the same parameters will lead to the creation "
"of the same dictionary."
msgstr ""
"当训练集大于最大内存时，CLI 将在可用样本中随机选取样本，直到达到所允许的最大"
"内存预算。这样做是为了通过减轻聚集所带来的潜在影响来提高字典的相关性，例如避"
"免只选取按修改日期排序或按字母顺序排序的列表开头的文件。该随机化过程是确定性"
"的，因此使用相同参数训练相同的文件列表将会创建出相同的字典。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:459
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<--dictID=#>"
msgstr "B<--dictID=#>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:462
msgid ""
"A dictionary ID is a locally unique ID. The decoder will use this value to "
"verify it is using the right dictionary. By default, zstd will create a 4-"
"bytes random number ID. It\\'s possible to provide an explicit number ID "
"instead. It\\'s up to the dictionary manager to not assign twice the same ID "
"to 2 different dictionaries. Note that short numbers have an advantage: an "
"ID E<lt> 256 will only need 1 byte in the compressed frame header, and an ID "
"E<lt> 65536 will only need 2 bytes. This compares favorably to 4 bytes "
"default."
msgstr ""
"字典 ID 是一个在本地唯一的 ID。解码器将使用此值来验证它所使用的字典是否正确。"
"默认情况下，zstd 会创建一个 4 字节的随机数 ID。也可以改为提供一个明确的数字 "
"ID。由字典管理者负责确保不会将同一个 ID 分配给两个不同的字典。请注意，较小的"
"数字有一个优势：ID E<lt> 256 在压缩帧头部中只需 1 字节，ID E<lt> 65536 只需 "
"2 字节。这相比默认的 4 字节更有优势。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:465
msgid ""
"Note that RFC8878 reserves IDs less than 32768 and greater than or equal to "
"2^31, so they should not be used in public."
msgstr ""
"请注意，RFC8878 保留了小于 32768 以及大于或等于 2^31 的 ID，因此它们不应在公"
"开场合使用。"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:466
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<--train-cover[=k#,d=#,steps=#,split=#,shrink[=#]]>"
msgstr "B<--train-cover[=k#,d=#,steps=#,split=#,shrink[=#]]>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:469
msgid ""
"Select parameters for the default dictionary builder algorithm named cover. "
"If I<d> is not specified, then it tries I<d> = 6 and I<d> = 8. If I<k> is "
"not specified, then it tries I<steps> values in the range [50, 2000]. If "
"I<steps> is not specified, then the default value of 40 is used. If I<split> "
"is not specified or split E<lt>= 0, then the default value of 100 is used. "
"Requires that I<d> E<lt>= I<k>. If I<shrink> flag is not used, then the "
"default value for I<shrinkDict> of 0 is used. If I<shrink> is not specified, "
"then the default value for I<shrinkDictMaxRegression> of 1 is used."
msgstr ""
"为名为 cover 的默认字典构建器算法选择参数。如果未指定 I<d>，则会尝试 I<d> = "
"6 和 I<d> = 8。如果未指定 I<k>，则会在 [50, 2000] 范围内尝试 I<steps> 个取"
"值。如果未指定 I<steps>，则使用默认值 40。如果未指定 I<split> 或 split "
"E<lt>= 0，则使用默认值 100。要求 I<d> E<lt>= I<k>。如果未使用 I<shrink> 标"
"志，则使用 I<shrinkDict> 的默认值 0。如果未指定 I<shrink>，则使用 "
"I<shrinkDictMaxRegression> 的默认值 1。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:472
msgid ""
"Selects segments of size I<k> with highest score to put in the dictionary. "
"The score of a segment is computed by the sum of the frequencies of all the "
"subsegments of size I<d>. Generally I<d> should be in the range [6, 8], "
"occasionally up to 16, but the algorithm will run faster with d E<lt>= I<8>. "
"Good values for I<k> vary widely based on the input data, but a safe range "
"is [2 * I<d>, 2000]. If I<split> is 100, all input samples are used for both "
"training and testing to find optimal I<d> and I<k> to build dictionary. "
"Supports multithreading if B<zstd> is compiled with threading support. "
"Having I<shrink> enabled takes a truncated dictionary of minimum size and "
"doubles in size until compression ratio of the truncated dictionary is at "
"most I<shrinkDictMaxRegression%> worse than the compression ratio of the "
"largest dictionary."
msgstr ""
"选取得分最高的、大小为 I<k> 的片段放入字典。一个片段的得分由所有大小为 I<d> "
"的子片段的频率之和计算得出。通常 I<d> 应在 [6, 8] 范围内，偶尔可高达 16，但"
"当 d E<lt>= I<8> 时算法运行得更快。I<k> 的合适取值因输入数据而有很大差异，但"
"一个安全的范围是 [2 * I<d>, 2000]。如果 I<split> 为 100，则所有输入样本都会同"
"时用于训练和测试，以找到用于构建字典的最优 I<d> 和 I<k>。如果编译 B<zstd> 时"
"启用了线程支持，则支持多线程。启用 I<shrink> 时，会取一个最小大小的截断字典，"
"并将其大小翻倍，直到该截断字典的压缩率与最大字典的压缩率相比最多差 "
"I<shrinkDictMaxRegression%>。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:475 raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:506 raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:519
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr "示例："

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:478
msgid "B<zstd --train-cover FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-cover FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:481
msgid "B<zstd --train-cover=k=50,d=8 FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-cover=k=50,d=8 FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:484
msgid "B<zstd --train-cover=d=8,steps=500 FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-cover=d=8,steps=500 FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:487
msgid "B<zstd --train-cover=k=50 FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-cover=k=50 FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:490
msgid "B<zstd --train-cover=k=50,split=60 FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-cover=k=50,split=60 FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:493
msgid "B<zstd --train-cover=shrink FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-cover=shrink FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:496
msgid "B<zstd --train-cover=shrink=2 FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-cover=shrink=2 FILEs>"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:497
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<--train-fastcover[=k#,d=#,f=#,steps=#,split=#,accel=#]>"
msgstr "B<--train-fastcover[=k#,d=#,f=#,steps=#,split=#,accel=#]>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:500
msgid ""
"Same as cover but with extra parameters I<f> and I<accel> and different "
"default value of split If I<split> is not specified, then it tries I<split> "
"= 75. If I<f> is not specified, then it tries I<f> = 20. Requires that 0 "
"E<lt> I<f> E<lt> 32. If I<accel> is not specified, then it tries I<accel> = "
"1. Requires that 0 E<lt> I<accel> E<lt>= 10. Requires that I<d> = 6 or I<d> "
"= 8."
msgstr ""
"与 cover 相同，但带有额外的参数 I<f> 和 I<accel>，且 split 的默认值不同。如果"
"未指定 I<split>，则会尝试 I<split> = 75。如果未指定 I<f>，则会尝试 I<f> = "
"20。要求 0 E<lt> I<f> E<lt> 32。如果未指定 I<accel>，则会尝试 I<accel> = 1。"
"要求 0 E<lt> I<accel> E<lt>= 10。要求 I<d> = 6 或 I<d> = 8。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:503
msgid ""
"I<f> is log of size of array that keeps track of frequency of subsegments of "
"size I<d>. The subsegment is hashed to an index in the range [0,2^I<f> - 1]. "
"It is possible that 2 different subsegments are hashed to the same index, "
"and they are considered as the same subsegment when computing frequency. "
"Using a higher I<f> reduces collision but takes longer."
msgstr ""
"I<f> 是用于跟踪大小为 I<d> 的子片段频率的数组大小的对数。子片段被哈希到 "
"[0,2^I<f> - 1] 范围内的一个索引。两个不同的子片段有可能被哈希到同一个索引，此"
"时在计算频率时它们会被视为同一个子片段。使用更高的 I<f> 会减少冲突，但耗时更"
"长。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:509
msgid "B<zstd --train-fastcover FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-fastcover FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:512
msgid "B<zstd --train-fastcover=d=8,f=15,accel=2 FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-fastcover=d=8,f=15,accel=2 FILEs>"

#. type: TP
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:513
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<--train-legacy[=selectivity=#]>"
msgstr "B<--train-legacy[=selectivity=#]>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:516
msgid ""
"Use legacy dictionary builder algorithm with the given dictionary "
"I<selectivity> (default: 9). The smaller the I<selectivity> value, the "
"denser the dictionary, improving its efficiency but reducing its achievable "
"maximum size. B<--train-legacy=s=#> is also accepted."
msgstr ""
"使用旧版字典构建器算法，并采用给定的字典 I<selectivity>（默认值：9）。"
"I<selectivity> 值越小，字典越密集，从而提高其效率但会降低其可达到的最大大小。"
"也接受 B<--train-legacy=s=#>。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:522
msgid "B<zstd --train-legacy FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-legacy FILEs>"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:525
msgid "B<zstd --train-legacy=selectivity=8 FILEs>"
msgstr "B<zstd --train-legacy=selectivity=8 FILEs>"

#. type: SH
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:526
#, no-wrap
msgid "BENCHMARK"
msgstr "基准测试"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:528
msgid ""
"The B<zstd> CLI provides a benchmarking mode that can be used to easily find "
"suitable compression parameters, or alternatively to benchmark a "
"computer\\'s performance. B<zstd -b [FILE(s)]> will benchmark B<zstd> for "
"both compression and decompression using default compression level. Note "
"that results are very dependent on the content being compressed."
msgstr ""
"B<zstd> 命令行工具提供了一种基准测试模式，可用于轻松找到合适的压缩参数，或者"
"用于对计算机的性能进行基准测试。B<zstd -b [FILE(s)]> 将使用默认压缩级别对 "
"B<zstd> 的压缩和解压缩进行基准测试。请注意，结果在很大程度上取决于所压缩的内"
"容。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:531
msgid ""
"It\\'s possible to pass multiple files to the benchmark, and even a "
"directory with B<-r DIRECTORY>. When no B<FILE> is provided, the benchmark "
"will use a procedurally generated B<lorem ipsum> text."
msgstr ""
"可以向基准测试传递多个文件，甚至可以用 B<-r DIRECTORY> 传递一个目录。当未提"
"供 B<FILE> 时，基准测试将使用程序化生成的 B<lorem ipsum> 文本。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:534
msgid ""
"Benchmarking will employ B<max(1, min(4, nbCores/4))> worker threads by "
"default in order to match the behavior of the normal CLI I/O."
msgstr ""
"为了与普通命令行 I/O 的行为保持一致，基准测试默认将使用 B<max(1, min(4, "
"nbCores/4))> 个工作线程。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:537
msgid "B<-b#>: benchmark file(s) using compression level #"
msgstr "B<-b#>：使用压缩级别 # 对文件进行基准测试"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:540
msgid ""
"B<-e#>: benchmark file(s) using multiple compression levels, from B<-b#> to "
"B<-e#> (inclusive)"
msgstr ""
"B<-e#>：使用多个压缩级别对文件进行基准测试，从 B<-b#> 到 B<-e#>（含两端）"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:543
msgid ""
"B<-d>: benchmark decompression speed only (requires providing a zstd-"
"compressed content)"
msgstr "B<-d>：仅对解压缩速度进行基准测试（需要提供 zstd 压缩过的内容）"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:546
msgid ""
"B<-i#>: minimum evaluation time, in seconds (default: 3s), benchmark mode "
"only"
msgstr "B<-i#>：最短评估时间，以秒为单位（默认值：3 秒），仅用于基准测试模式"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:549
msgid ""
"B<-B#>, B<--block-size=#>: cut file(s) into independent chunks of size # "
"(default: no chunking)"
msgstr ""
"B<-B#>, B<--block-size=#>：将文件切分为大小为 # 的独立块（默认值：不切分）"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:552
msgid ""
"B<-S>: output one benchmark result per input file (default: consolidated "
"result)"
msgstr "B<-S>：为每个输入文件输出一个基准测试结果（默认值：汇总结果）"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:555
msgid "B<-D dictionary> benchmark using dictionary"
msgstr "B<-D dictionary>：使用字典进行基准测试"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:558
msgid "B<--priority=rt>: set process priority to real-time (Windows)"
msgstr "B<--priority=rt>：将进程优先级设置为实时（Windows）"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:563
msgid ""
"Beyond compression levels, benchmarking is also compatible with other "
"parameters, such as number of threads (B<-T#>), advanced compression "
"parameters (B<--zstd=###>), dictionary compression (B<-D dictionary>), or "
"even disabling checksum verification for example."
msgstr ""
"除了压缩级别之外，基准测试还兼容其他参数，例如线程数（B<-T#>）、高级压缩参数"
"（B<--zstd=###>）、字典压缩（B<-D dictionary>），甚至可以禁用校验和验证等。"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:566
msgid ""
"B<Output Format:> CompressionLevel#Filename: InputSize -E<gt> OutputSize "
"(CompressionRatio), CompressionSpeed, DecompressionSpeed"
msgstr ""
"B<输出格式：> 压缩级别#文件名: 输入大小 -E<gt> 输出大小 (压缩率), 压缩速度, "
"解压缩速度"

#. type: Plain text
#: raw/zstd/man1/zstd.1:569
msgid ""
"B<Methodology:> For speed measurement, the entire input is compressed/"
"decompressed in-memory to measure speed. A run lasts at least 1 sec, so when "
"files are small, they are compressed/decompressed several times per run, in "
"order to improve measurement accuracy."
msgstr ""
"B<方法：> 对于速度测量，整个输入会在内存中被压缩/解压缩以测量速度。一次运行至"
"少持续 1 秒，因此当文件较小时，每次运行会对它们进行多次压缩/解压缩，以提高测"
"量的准确性。"

